                    <li>TLS encryption</li>
                    <li>App Password authentication</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="info-box">
            <h4>üìå SMTP Implementation Details</h4>
            <p><strong>Direct SMTP for MVP:</strong> This implementation uses Gmail's SMTP server directly without third-party email services (SendGrid, Mailgun, AWS SES).</p>
            
            <div class="pros-cons">
                <div class="pros">
                    <h4>‚úÖ Advantages</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Free (no service costs)</li>
                        <li>Simple setup</li>
                        <li>Perfect for MVP testing</li>
                        <li>No API integrations needed</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="cons">
                    <h4>‚ùå Limitations</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Gmail rate limits (~500/day)</li>
                        <li>Lower deliverability vs dedicated services</li>
                        <li>No email analytics (opens/clicks)</li>
                        <li>Account suspension risk for mass sending</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

